250 g Ground Beef
350 g Yellow Potato
⅓ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
1 unit(s) Zucchini
56.5 g Corn Kernels
1 unit(s) Red Onion
56 g Edamame
7 g Parsley
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
½ tbsp Oil*
½ tsp Salt*
½ tsp Pepper*

Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add potatoes, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil and Zesty Garlic Blend to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Arrange potatoes on a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast in the bottom of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 22-25 min.

Meanwhile, line another baking sheet with parchment paper.
Finely chop parsley.
Add beef, half the feta, half the parsley, half the Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend and panko to a large bowl. Season with 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) pepper, then combine.
Roll mixture into 12 (24) equal-sized meatballs).

Arrange meatballs on the prepared baking sheet.
Bake in the middle of the oven until golden-brown and cooked through, 12-14 min.**

Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
Halve zucchini lengthwise, then cut into 1/2-inch half-moons.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then edamame, red onion and half the corn (use all for 4 ppl). Cook, stirring often, until starting to brown, 2 min. Add zucchini and 1/2 cup (1 cup) water. Season with salt, pepper and remaining Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend. Cook, stirring often, until water evaporates and veggies are tender-crisp, 3-4 min.
Remove from heat.

Once the potatoes have finished roasting, transfer veggies to the same baking sheet, then stir to combine the potatoes and veggies.
Divide meatballs and potato succotash between plates.
Drizzle chipotle sauce meatballs.
Sprinkle remaining feta and remaining parsley over succotash.

If you've opted to get beef, prep and cook it in the same way the recipe instructs you to prep and cook the turkey.**